  "activityType": "pronunciation",
  "title": "The Buzzing 'TH' and Sneaky 'S'",
  "learningGoal": "The learner will master the voiced dental fricative (/ð/) in demonstratives (preventing 'dis/dat' substitutions) and accurately distinguish between the short /ɪ/ in 'this' and the long /i:/ in 'these'.",
  "difficultyLevel": "beginner",
  "baseLanguage": "hi",
  "targetLanguage": "en",
  "estimatedTime": 45,
  "prerequisites": ["en_hi_M2B5_lesson_001"],
  "instructions": "This lesson attacks two hard sounds. First, the 'TH' in This/That/These/Those. It is NOT a 'D' sound. You must buzz your tongue on your top teeth like a bee! Second, the difference between This and These. 'This' is short and fast. 'These' is long and ends in a 'Z' sound like a bee!",
  "contentItems": [
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "CRITICAL: Do not say 'Dis is my pen'. Put the tip of your tongue slightly UNDER your top teeth and blow air to make the buzzing TH sound."
    }
  ],
